# React-atsiskaitymas-2023.02.02
A simple registration and login system using React and fetch API.

## Getting Started
These instructions will get you a copy of the project up and running on your local machine for development and testing purposes.

## Prerequisites
What things you need to install the software and how to install them:

Node.js
npm (node package manager)
Installing
## Clone the repository to your local machine :
git clone https://github.com/<ryckabass0827>/React-atsiskaitymas-2023.02.02.git
  
## Change into the project directory : 
  cd React\ atsiskaitymas/atsiskaitymas
  
## Install the required dependencies 
 __ npm install __
 __ npm i react-router-dom __
 __ npm i json-server __
 
 ## Start the server
 __ json-server --watch data.json __
  
  ## Start the development server
  npm start
  
 ## Open the app in your browser at http://localhost:3001
  
 ## Functionality
User can register with email and password
User can log in with email and password
The user will be redirected to the home page after successful login
If the email is already registered, the user will be notified
If the passwords don't match during registration, the user will be notified
  
 ## Notes
The app uses a JSON file as a mock database for storing users
The fetch requests are made to http://localhost:3000/users and http://localhost:3000/posts
